  2. The Key Difference: Real-Time Validation

  When I code:
  1. I edit file
  2. Save file
  3. Run TypeScript compiler
  4. See errors
  5. Fix errors
  6. Repeat...

  When Cline codes:
  1. Cline types code
  2. VS Code shows errors IMMEDIATELY (red squiggles)
  3. Cline sees errors BEFORE saving
  4. Cline fixes them on the spot
  5. Only saves when clean

  Cline has VS Code's TypeScript language server running in real-time!

